                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, March 3: A Reserve Bank expert group has suggested that banks be given a greater role in interest rates futures (IRF) because restricting them to hedging will impair liquidity in the market. The irf market depends on a significant presence of all classes of participants. Banks not only occupy commanding heights in the financial sector but also possess the necessary technical expertise for fulfilling the role of an informed, disciplined and regulated participated class, the working group said in its report.                            
